available on GitHub. You are permitted to:

  ✔  Read, study, and learn from the source code.
  ✔  Download and run the software for personal use at no cost.
  ✔  Modify the source code for personal, educational, or non-commercial use.
  ✔  Fork the repository and build derivative works.

If you distribute a modified version of Playitfy to any third party — whether
as source code, a compiled binary, or any other form — you MUST:

  ①  Release the complete corresponding source code of your modified version
      under the same GPLv3 license, publicly and at no charge.

  ②  Clearly state that your version is a derivative of Playitfy and provide
      a link to the original repository:
        https://github.com/gantarugavr/Playitfy

  ③  Preserve this license file in its entirety within your distribution.

You are PROHIBITED from:

  ✘  Re-licensing this software or any derivative under a proprietary,
     closed-source, or non-GPLv3-compatible license.
  ✘  Selling the software itself or a derivative as a paid product without
     releasing the full source code under GPLv3.
  ✘  Removing or replacing the copyright notice of the original author.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  CLAUSE II — FORCED ATTRIBUTION (Anti-Plagiarism Logic)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Playitfy contains an embedded attribution guard within its source code.
The footer string:

    "© 2026 Project ❄️ gantarugavr.me"

is bound to the application's runtime integrity. The program performs a
continuous self-check every 200 milliseconds. If the footer text is altered
or removed at runtime, the application will immediately terminate itself.

This mechanism exists as a logical filter, not as a DRM restriction.
Any developer who studies the source code will understand and respect it.
Plagiarists who blindly copy the code without reading it will encounter
automatic failure upon execution.

The following actions are explicitly prohibited:

  ✘  Modifying or removing the footer attribution string in a distributed build
     without replacing it with a clearly visible attribution notice crediting
     the original author (gantarugavr.me) within the application UI.
  ✘  Redistributing the application binary or source with the intent to
     misrepresent authorship.

If you create a legitimate fork with visible credit to the original author
and your own identity, you may adapt the footer text accordingly, provided
the original attribution remains somewhere visible in the application.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  CLAUSE III — DISTRIBUTION INTEGRITY (End-User Protection)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The official compiled binary (app.exe) released by gantarugavr.me is protected
by a SHA-256 hash checksum embedded within the executable itself.

Upon launch, the application verifies that its own binary has not been tampered
with. If the hash does not match the expected value, the application will
refuse to run.

This mechanism exists solely to protect end-users. Its purpose is:

  ①  To ensure that any binary circulating under the name "Playitfy" and
      claiming to be an official release has not been modified to contain
      malware, trojans, spyware, or any unauthorized code.

  ②  To protect the reputation of the original developer. If a malicious actor
      injects harmful code into the official binary and redistributes it,
      the integrity check will catch it and prevent execution.

This clause applies specifically to binaries distributed as official releases.
Developers building from source for personal use or legitimate forks are
naturally exempt — their own compiled binary will carry their own hash.

The following actions are prohibited:

  ✘  Distributing a modified version of the official app.exe while claiming
     it is an unmodified official release from gantarugavr.me.
  ✘  Stripping or bypassing the integrity check in a redistribution with
     the intent to spread modified binaries under the original author's name.


